title.narrative: Maternal Neonatal and Child Health Project

description.narrative: (Pakistan): The Maternal, Neonatal, and Child Health Services Project aims to improve access, quality, and coverage of key MCH services for rural and marginalized communities in Sindh in support of an overall goal of "Improving Maternal and Child Health Outcomes in Targeted Areas." FY15 funds will: 1) expand the quality of MNCH service delivery from 10 to 15 districts in the target province of Sindh; 2) refurbish approximately 200 public sector facilities; 3) scale-up use of high-impact, best practices, such as community use of misoprostol and; 4) train providers on basic and comprehensive emergency obstetric and neonatal care across 600 public and private sector facilities.This investment will increase the capacity of the public and private sectors to deliver high quality reproductive and MNCH services to further increase coverage of life-saving interventions. This will ultimately result in an accelerated decrease in maternal and infant mortality.
